
Libtool manages the creation and installation of static and dynamic libraries.

Libtool is supposed to facilitate the complexity of using shared libraries by wrapping them into a consistent and platform independent interface.

{ .la files

  
   → development/filename-extensions#la[`.la`] files are libtool archive files. They're generally not needed on a → Linux system.

}

sa:
  → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System[GNU Build System]

  → Linux/fhs/usr/share/libtool and
  → Linux/fhs/usr/include/libltdl
